{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout mirrors the reference image, employing a single-column structure for clarity and ease of navigation on smaller screens.  Sections are clearly delineated using spacing to guide the user's eye through the login process. Top-level actions are positioned prominently for immediate accessibility, while secondary and tertiary actions are placed in logical order, below the primary call-to-actions.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow prioritizes direct mobile number login, followed by convenient social login options.  Password recovery and legal links are clearly visible but are secondary actions to avoid cluttering the primary authentication path. Error handling is implied through placeholder space for error messages.",
    "componentChoices": "Components are chosen from the design system to ensure visual consistency.  The InputSingleline component is used for mobile number input with a built-in country code selector (Select component). The Button component is used for the primary 'Continue' button and styled as an elevated button. Social login buttons are implemented using the respective Google, Apple, and Facebook design system components. The Link component renders legal text.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through prominence of primary actions, strategic spacing, and typography.  The 'Continue' button and mobile number input are styled with high visual emphasis. Secondary social login options are grouped together but receive less visual emphasis. The legal text at the bottom is styled as caption text.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "Variants are selected based on the user's intent and the importance of each element. The 'Continue' button utilizes an elevated style for prominence. Input fields for the mobile number use default filled states.  Social buttons use default active states. The 'Forgot Password' option employs a secondary style link, maintaining visual consistency with the design system. Legal links are rendered as caption-styled links."
  }
}
